chore: update Docker image metadata and install requirements
- Add a note specifying that git-credential-manager requires .NET 8 - Update vendor label from "containertoolbx" to "Fedora Project" - Add detailed labels for the container image, including summary, description, and license information
Signed-off-by: CHEN, CHUN <jim60105@gmail.com>

docs: enhance README with detailed tool descriptions
- Expand the README with a detailed explanation of Toolbx and its usage. - Add aria2 to the Fedora Toolbox image. - Update toolbox section headings with links to their respective websites.
Signed-off-by: CHEN, CHUN <jim60105@gmail.com>

feat(video): add Anime4K for enhanced video rendering quality
- Add `jq` to the list of required tools in the README. - Add `Anime4K` to the list of video tools in the README. - Add `jq` installation in `base.Containerfile`. - Add a new build stage for `Anime4K` in `video.Containerfile`. - Copy `Anime4K` shaders to the final image in `video.Containerfile`. - Add keybindings for Anime4K shader mode
Signed-off-by: CHEN, CHUN <jim60105@gmail.com>

feat: add toolbox runners for improved command execution
- Add command to copy files from `/copy-to-host` to `~/.local/bin` in multiple toolbox setups - Copy toolbox runners to `/copy-to-host` in several Containerfile configurations - Update desktop entry files to simplify the execution command, removing the toolbox wrapper - Create new runner scripts for applications like `aria2c`, `datagrip`, `rider`, `rustrover`, `sourcegit`, and video tools (`ffmpeg`, `ffprobe`, `mpv`, `yt-dlp`)
Signed-off-by: CHEN, CHUN <jim60105@gmail.com>

feat: streamline VSCode execution with new toolbox runner
- Add a command in the README to copy files to `~/.local/bin` in the VSCode toolbox section. - Remove the setup script for VSCode in the `sourcegit.Containerfile`. - Add a step to copy the `vscode/runner` script to `/copy-to-host` in the `vscode.Containerfile`. - Simplify the `Exec` command in the `vscode/desktop/code.desktop` file to directly call `code`. - Add a new script in `vscode/runner/code` to run VSCode with Wayland support in a toolbox environment.
Signed-off-by: CHEN, CHUN <jim60105@gmail.com>

feat: add DataGrip toolbox
- Add a GitHub Actions workflow to build and push a DataGrip container image. - Update VSCode settings to include "datagrip" in the cSpell words list. - Add DataGrip toolbox instructions to the README. - Include DataGrip in the toolbox cheat sheet for recreating all toolboxes. - Create a `datagrip.Containerfile` for building the DataGrip co
Signed-off-by: CHEN, CHUN <jim60105@gmail.com>
